My basic .vim setup

Setup

  git clone git://github.com/gberenfield/dotvim.git

  ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
  ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc

  cd ~/.vim
  git submodule init
  git submodule update

Maintenance

  Apparently, the helpfile system when using bundled plugins via pathogens causes git submodules to become dirty.
  Per http://www.nils-haldenwang.de/frameworks-and-tools/git/how-to-ignore-changes-in-git-submodules
  adding "ignore = dirty" to each pathogen plugin in .gitmodules fixes this annoyance.

  Upgrading all bundled plugins

    You can use the foreach command to execute any shell script in from the root of all submodule directories. To update to the latest version of each plugin bundle, run the following:
    --> git submodule foreach git pull origin master


Opening files nicely

  Removed command-t. Not for me.

  Use peepopen (if on mac) or molly instead


